Even under a very optimistic scenario it will take several decades for the poor toÂ reach the income level of the global top 10%.

2% is roughly the growth rate that the richest countries of today experienced over the last decades (<a href="https://ourworldindata.org/economic-growth#economic-growth-at-the-technological-frontier-growth-in-the-usa">see here</a>).Â We have seen that poorer countries can achieve faster growth, but we have not seen growth rates ofÂ more thanÂ 6% over a time frame as long as necessary to reach the level of the global 10%Â in such a short time. If the past is a good guide for the future the world will very likely be highly unequal for a long time.
